Today is Transgender Day of Visibility. 🏳️‍⚧️🏳️‍⚧️🏳️‍⚧️With the recent and not so recent attacks on trans folks occurring across the country, visibility is more important than ever. So today and every other day many trans folks with the privilege, access or safety to do so are creating visibility for those who cannot safely be themselves without losing their jobs, housing and much more. And right now, most importantly, for those who are children growing up with ignorant cisgender lawmakers doing everything they can to erase trans kids’ identities and access to lifesaving healthcare. Transgender folks have always existed and will continue to exist regardless of how hard cis folks try to erase us. Our existence is not a threat, so stop wasting excessive time and money and instead put all of that hateful energy towards erasing the real threats. Hint: It’s not drag queens or trans kids. 
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#transgenderdayofvisibility #trans #lgbt #visibility #wearentgoinganywhere #weexist #werenotgoinganywhere
